GN   Name=INS;
OS   Homo sapiens (Human).
OC   Eukaryota; Metazoa; Chordata; Craniata; Vertebrata; Euteleostomi; Mammalia;
OC   Eutheria; Euarchontoglires; Primates; Haplorrhini; Catarrhini; Hominidae;
OC   Homo.
OX   NCBI_TaxID=9606;
CC   -!- FUNCTION: Insulin decreases blood glucose concentration. It increases
CC       cell permeability to monosaccharides, amino acids and fatty acids. It
CC       accelerates glycolysis, the pentose phosphate cycle, and glycogen
CC       synthesis in liver.
CC   -!- SUBUNIT: Heterodimer of a B chain and an A chain linked by two
CC       disulfide bonds (PubMed:25423173). {ECO:0000269|PubMed:25423173}.
CC   -!- INTERACTION:
CC       P01308; Q6UY14-3: ADAMTSL4; NbExp=3; IntAct=EBI-7090529, EBI-10173507;
CC       P01308; A8MQ03: CYSRT1; NbExp=3; IntAct=EBI-7090529, EBI-3867333;
CC       P01308; P14735-1: IDE; NbExp=3; IntAct=EBI-7090529, EBI-15607031;
CC       P01308; P01308: INS; NbExp=19; IntAct=EBI-7090529, EBI-7090529;
CC       P01308; P06213-2: INSR; NbExp=6; IntAct=EBI-7090529, EBI-9984921;
CC       P01308; Q07627: KRTAP1-1; NbExp=3; IntAct=EBI-7090529, EBI-11959885;
CC       P01308; Q8IUG1: KRTAP1-3; NbExp=3; IntAct=EBI-7090529, EBI-11749135;
CC       P01308; P0DPK4: NOTCH2NLC; NbExp=3; IntAct=EBI-7090529, EBI-22310682;
CC       PRO_0000015820; P11142: HSPA8; NbExp=2; IntAct=EBI-20765227, EBI-351896;
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted {ECO:0000269|PubMed:36309486}.
CC   -!- ALTERNATIVE PRODUCTS:
CC       Event=Alternative splicing; Named isoforms=2;
CC       Name=1;
CC         IsoId=P01308-1; Sequence=Displayed;
CC       Name=2; Synonyms=INS-IGF2;
CC         IsoId=F8WCM5-1; Sequence=External;
CC   -!- TISSUE SPECIFICITY: Expressed by pancreatic beta-cells (at protein
CC       level). {ECO:0000269|PubMed:36309486}.
CC   -!- DISEASE: Hyperproinsulinemia (HPRI) [MIM:616214]: An autosomal dominant
CC       condition characterized by elevated levels of serum proinsulin-like
CC       material. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:1601997, ECO:0000269|PubMed:2196279,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:3470784, ECO:0000269|PubMed:4019786,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:6312455, ECO:0000269|PubMed:6424111,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:8421693}. Note=The disease is caused by variants
CC       affecting the gene represented in this entry.
CC   -!- DISEASE: Type 1 diabetes mellitus 2 (T1D2) [MIM:125852]: A
CC       multifactorial disorder of glucose homeostasis that is characterized by
CC       susceptibility to ketoacidosis in the absence of insulin therapy.
CC       Clinical features are polydipsia, polyphagia and polyuria which result
CC       from hyperglycemia-induced osmotic diuresis and secondary thirst. These
CC       derangements result in long-term complications that affect the eyes,
CC       kidneys, nerves, and blood vessels. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:18192540}.
CC       Note=The disease is caused by variants affecting the gene represented
CC       in this entry.
CC   -!- DISEASE: Diabetes mellitus, permanent neonatal, 4 (PNDM4) [MIM:618858]:
CC       A form of permanent neonatal diabetes mellitus, a type of diabetes
CC       characterized by onset of persistent hyperglycemia within the first six
CC       months of life. Initial clinical manifestations include intrauterine
CC       growth retardation, hyperglycemia, glycosuria, osmotic polyuria, severe
CC       dehydration, and failure to thrive. PNDM4 transmission pattern is
CC       consistent with autosomal dominant or autosomal recessive inheritance.
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:17855560, ECO:0000269|PubMed:18162506}. Note=The
CC       disease is caused by variants affecting the gene represented in this
CC       entry.
CC   -!- DISEASE: Maturity-onset diabetes of the young 10 (MODY10) [MIM:613370]:
CC       A form of diabetes that is characterized by an autosomal dominant mode
CC       of inheritance, onset in childhood or early adulthood (usually before
CC       25 years of age), a primary defect in insulin secretion and frequent
CC       insulin-independence at the beginning of the disease.
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:18162506, ECO:0000269|PubMed:18192540,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:20226046, ECO:0000269|PubMed:25423173}. Note=The
CC       disease is caused by variants affecting the gene represented in this
CC       entry.
CC   -!- PHARMACEUTICAL: Available under the names Humulin or Humalog (Eli
CC       Lilly) and Novolin (Novo Nordisk). Used in the treatment of diabetes.
CC       Humalog is an insulin analog with 52-Lys-Pro-53 instead of 52-Pro-Lys-
CC       53.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the insulin family. {ECO:0000305}.
CC   -!- SEQUENCE CAUTION:
CC       Sequence=AAA59179.1; Type=Erroneous gene model prediction; Evidence={ECO:0000305};
